"Technology is just a tool. In terms of getting the kids working together and motivating them, the teacher is the most important." ~ Bill Gates

Celebrated annually on September 5 to mark the birthday of Dr Sarvepalli Radhakrishnan, this day is marked to pay tribute to the most respected profession, that is, teaching. To the teachers who work tirelessly to teach us concepts, to the teachers who sacrifice their own sleep and meals for the sake of students, to the teachers who say that they couldn't have their meal as they were clearing doubts of students, to those who used to settle disputes when we were kids, to those who taught us moral values, to those who used to take classes despite us being so distracted and irritated, to those who taught us how to play different sports, to those who taught us how to contain our emotions, to those who used to advise us how to deal in case of disputes, we owe you big time. Our respect and benevolence for you will always fall short compared to what you have given us.  

ISTE NIT Durgapur feels privileged to be able to express our heartfelt respect for mentors like you and wishes a very happy Teachers' Day to all the teachers of knowledge, education and of life.

#iste #happy #teachers #day #guru #blessings #education #lifebuilders

Oxygen helps us breathe but what keeps us alive is faith. And when it comes to laying your faith on, no one is better than God. Lord Krishna, a divinity who is juvenile enough to make us giggle and who is supreme enough that he needs no weapon to turn the most catastrophic war topsy turvy.

Janmashtami is a salient Hindu festival that celebrates the birth of Krishna. It is marked every year on the eighth day of the Krishna Paksha in Shraavana and Bhadrapada. The eighth incarnation of Lord Vishnu, son of Devaki and Vasudev, Krishna’s folktales and folklores are omnipresent in the Sanatana dharma. The Krishna Leela covers the various stages of his life on earth. The Geeta, the holy Hindu book, which has the answer to every possible question, is the exact words of Krishna from the Kurukshetra of Mahabharata. With greatness in his every word and divineness in his every glance , admiration for him knows no limit.

So, on this day, we here at ISTE NIT DURGAPUR, with our hearts sanctified by his grace, wish everyone a very soothing Janmashtami. May Lord Krishna bless you with peace and calmness.

#happyjanmashtami #iste #matkiphod

Hi fellas!! ISTE NIT Durgapur welcomes you to an all new stunning and mind boggling event, CRYPTONOVA. 
🔍🖥️🔎
Unravel the puzzels that lay hidden beneath the mysterious cryptographic codes and ciphers. 

💡💡💡💡💡

The event has been divided into two stages. 

ROUND 1:- Some ciphers and cryptographic codes will be given as questions, solving which the participants will get a sentence which would act as the password to unlock the next stage. Unless answered correctly the questions of next round will not be displayed. 

Hints for round 1 will be given after 15 mins of start of the event on our social media handles. 

ROUND 2:- This stage will consist of stories or problems related to various cryptographic techniques. From the situation provided, participants need to figure out the code and decrypt it. 

Hints for  round 2 will be displayed after 30 mins of start of the event, on our social media handles. 

🎉🎊 Exciting cash prizes await the winners. 🎊🎉

RULES :-

1️⃣ Register online in google forms. 

2️⃣ No.of stages :- 2.

3️⃣ Duration of the full event :- 1.5 hrs

4️⃣ All the answers must be in UPPERCASE letters.(Mandatory)

5️⃣ Commenting down the answers in the social media pages will lead to disqualification.

6️⃣ This event can be played in teams of two or can be played individually as well.

7️⃣ Keep checking our Social Media platforms for the hints.

An irreplaceable and intricate part of Hindu culture and festivities, Raksha Bandhan dates back to the time when the great Noble Laureate Rabindranath Tagore started a festival during the Partition of Bengal in 1905, where he encouraged Hindu and Muslim women to tie a rakhi on men from the other community and make them their brothers.

Raksha Bandhan also called simply as "Rakhi" is a glorious festival celebrated all over the country by the Hindu community with great pomp and zeal.According to the lunar calendar, this festival is observed on the day of the full moon in July or August, so also known as "Rakhi Purnima".Rakhi symbolizes love and harmony. On this auspicious day, the brothers take an oath to protect their sisters from anything or anyone harmful. The sisters pray for the well being of their brothers and then tie a band on their wrist to strengthen the oath, thereby completing the circle of eternal affection and bondage and finally exchanging gifts and presents. 

We here at ISTE NIT Durgapur wish everyone of you a very happy and memorable, colourful and pompous Rakhi Purnima from the depths of our heart.

Like the flora, my head is held high,
One day I want to escape like the butterfly.
It is time to be free and let our minds fly,
No sense of direction, just soar through the sky. 

“At the stroke of the midnight hour, when the world sleeps, India will awake to life and freedom,” Jawaharlal Nehru, the first Prime Minister of Independent India said on the night of August 15, 1947. 

India fought for its freedom and finally got it after 200 years of British rule. Later, to commemorate the occasion, the Indian national flag was hoisted above the Lahori Gate of Red Fort in Delhi. However, everything comes with a price. Around 14 million people had to abandon their homes during the India-Pakistan partition, when colonial British administrators began dismantling the empire in southern Asia. As we sing "Saare Jahan se accha, Hindustan humara", we pay tribute to those soldiers and all frontline workers who work relentlessly to uphold the nation's independence.  

 ISTE NIT Durgapur wishes everyone a Happy Independence Day. We hope that we can be victorious in our battle against the pandemic, just the way we did 75 years back against the British.

#happyindependenceday #india #iste #independence #freedom #15thaugust #tricolor #jaihind🇮🇳

Muharram is one of the most religious and emotional festivals of the Muslim community.It commemorates the first month of the Islamic Lunar calendar.  Imam Hussein, the son of Hazrat Ali and the grandson of Prophet Muhammad was killed in the battle of Karbala, which resulted in the eternal mourning of the Shia Muslim community.

The tenth day of the month,i.e the day of Ashura is marked as the day of grief by the Shia Muslim community.They fast for ten days and on the eleventh day, they mourn for the demise of Imam Hussein. As per the Sunni Muslim community, Muharram marks the day when Moses had conquered over the Egyptian Pharaoh (King) with his disciples. Some of the Muslim communities prepare sweet rice and share it with their family, friends and relatives.

We here at ISTE NIT Durgapur, with an essence of grief on this historically tragic day, wish everyone a solemn and heartfelt Muharram.

#iste #islamicnewyear #muharram #festival
